Contig: The name of the sequence (typically a chromosome) on which the variation is being called.
Position: The 1-based position of the variation on the given sequence.
Reference: The reference base (or bases in the case of an indel) at the given position on the given reference sequence.
Alternate Allele: The list of alternative alleles at this position.
TYPE: The type of allele, either snp, mnp, ins, del, or complex.
Effect: Most significant (negative) genotypic consequence of variant.
DP: Total read depth at the locus.
DPB: Total read depth per bp at the locus; bases in reads overlapping / bases in haplotype.
DPRA: Alternate allele depth ratio.  Ratio between depth in samples with each called alternate allele and those without.
Percentage of reads supporting the variant versus those supporting reference reads.
Allele frequency of variant from ExAC API.
